cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is primarily focused on video captioning, which is a task related to computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a reinforcement learning-based approach to select informative frames, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI another likely category. The paper also discusses the use of an encoder-decoder framework, which is a common technique in natural language processing, suggesting cs.CL (Computation and Language) as another possible category. The paper also mentions the reduction of computation cost, which is a concern in multimedia processing, indicating cs.MM (Multimedia) as another potential category. Finally, the paper uses a reward-based approach to select frames, which is a common technique in reinforcement learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible category.
